body_html:
At the same time, this is succeeding:

python -c 'from tensorflow.contrib.lite.toco.python import tensorflow_wrap_toco'

So I thought to compare the symbols.

(/private/tmp/scratch.nwani/1534993632/dev) ➜  1534993632 nm .//dev/lib/python2.7/site-packages/tensorflow/contrib/lite/toco/python/_tensorflow_wrap_toco.so | grep tensorflow_wrap_toco
0000000000003230 T _init_tensorflow_wrap_toco
                 U init_tensorflow_wrap_toco
                 I init_tensorflow_wrap_toco (indirect for init_tensorflow_wrap_toco)

(/private/tmp/scratch.nwani/1534993632/dev) ➜  1534993632 nm /private/tmp/scratch.nwani/1534993632/dev/lib/python2.7/site-packages/tensorflow/contrib/tensorrt/_wrap_conversion.so  | grep wrap_conversion
0000000000003670 t _init_wrap_conversion <---------- small 't' :(
                 U init_wrap_conversion
                 I init_wrap_conversion (indirect for init_wrap_conversion)

Then, I went on to build from source to see what is going on. Looking at the object files, I saw that both are capital 'T':

some-mac-box:~ nwani$ nm /private/var/tmp/_bazel_nwani/c8db850cfe278c8297aabaa8ebedf47a/execroot/org_tensorflow/bazel-out/darwin-opt/bin/tensorflow/contrib/tensorrt/_objs/_wrap_conversion.so/tensorflow/contrib/tensorrt/wrap_conversion.pic.o  | grep init_
00000000000005d0 T _init_wrap_conversion
some-mac-box:~ nwani$ nm /private/var/tmp/_bazel_nwani/c8db850cfe278c8297aabaa8ebedf47a/execroot/org_tensorflow/bazel-out/darwin-opt/bin/tensorflow/contrib/lite/toco/python/_objs/_tensorflow_wrap_toco.so/tensorflow/contrib/lite/toco/python/tensorflow_wrap_toco.pic.o | grep init_
0000000000000000 T _init_tensorflow_wrap_toco

But then in the genereated DSOs, I found that the trouble some one hides the init symbol :(

some-mac-box:~ nwani$ nm /private/var/tmp/_bazel_nwani/c8db850cfe278c8297aabaa8ebedf47a/execroot/org_tensorflow/bazel-out/darwin-opt/bin/tensorflow/tools/pip_package/simple_console.runfiles/org_tensorflow/tensorflow/contrib/lite/toco/python/_tensorflow_wrap_toco.so | grep init_tensor
0000000000002150 T _init_tensorflow_wrap_toco
                 I init_tensorflow_wrap_toco (indirect for init_tensorflow_wrap_toco)
                 U init_tensorflow_wrap_toco
some-mac-box:~ nwani$ nm /private/var/tmp/_bazel_nwani/c8db850cfe278c8297aabaa8ebedf47a/execroot/org_tensorflow/bazel-out/darwin-opt/bin/tensorflow/contrib/tensorrt/_wrap_conversion.so | grep init_wra
0000000000002e20 t _init_wrap_conversion <----- why you small 't'?
                 I init_wrap_conversion (indirect for init_wrap_conversion)
                 U init_wrap_conversion

Surprisingly, the versions scripts are identical:

some-mac-box:~ nwani$ diff /private/var/tmp/_bazel_nwani/c8db850cfe278c8297aabaa8ebedf47a/execroot/org_tensorflow/bazel-out/darwin-opt/bin/tensorflow/contrib/lite/toco/python/tensorflow_wrap_toco_versionscript.lds /private/var/tmp/_bazel_nwani/c8db850cfe278c8297aabaa8ebedf47a/execroot/org_tensorflow/bazel-out/darwin-opt/bin/tensorflow/contrib/tensorrt/wrap_conversion_versionscript.lds
2c2
< init_tensorflow_wrap_toco
---
> init_wrap_conversion

body:
At the same time, this is succeeding:
```
python -c 'from tensorflow.contrib.lite.toco.python import tensorflow_wrap_toco'
```
So I thought to compare the symbols.
```
(/private/tmp/scratch.nwani/1534993632/dev) ➜  1534993632 nm .//dev/lib/python2.7/site-packages/tensorflow/contrib/lite/toco/python/_tensorflow_wrap_toco.so | grep tensorflow_wrap_toco
0000000000003230 T _init_tensorflow_wrap_toco
                 U init_tensorflow_wrap_toco
                 I init_tensorflow_wrap_toco (indirect for init_tensorflow_wrap_toco)

(/private/tmp/scratch.nwani/1534993632/dev) ➜  1534993632 nm /private/tmp/scratch.nwani/1534993632/dev/lib/python2.7/site-packages/tensorflow/contrib/tensorrt/_wrap_conversion.so  | grep wrap_conversion
0000000000003670 t _init_wrap_conversion <---------- small 't' :(
                 U init_wrap_conversion
                 I init_wrap_conversion (indirect for init_wrap_conversion)
```
Then, I went on to build from source to see what is going on. Looking at the object files, I saw that both are capital 'T':
```
some-mac-box:~ nwani$ nm /private/var/tmp/_bazel_nwani/c8db850cfe278c8297aabaa8ebedf47a/execroot/org_tensorflow/bazel-out/darwin-opt/bin/tensorflow/contrib/tensorrt/_objs/_wrap_conversion.so/tensorflow/contrib/tensorrt/wrap_conversion.pic.o  | grep init_
00000000000005d0 T _init_wrap_conversion

0000000000000000 T _init_tensorflow_wrap_toco
```

But then in the genereated DSOs, I found that the trouble some one hides the init symbol :(
```
some-mac-box:~ nwani$ nm /private/var/tmp/_bazel_nwani/c8db850cfe278c8297aabaa8ebedf47a/execroot/org_tensorflow/bazel-out/darwin-opt/bin/tensorflow/tools/pip_package/simple_console.runfiles/org_tensorflow/tensorflow/contrib/lite/toco/python/_tensorflow_wrap_toco.so | grep init_tensor
0000000000002150 T _init_tensorflow_wrap_toco
                 I init_tensorflow_wrap_toco (indirect for init_tensorflow_wrap_toco)
                 U init_tensorflow_wrap_toco
some-mac-box:~ nwani$ nm /private/var/tmp/_bazel_nwani/c8db850cfe278c8297aabaa8ebedf47a/execroot/org_tensorflow/bazel-out/darwin-opt/bin/tensorflow/contrib/tensorrt/_wrap_conversion.so | grep init_wra
0000000000002e20 t _init_wrap_conversion <----- why you small 't'?
                 I init_wrap_conversion (indirect for init_wrap_conversion)
                 U init_wrap_conversion
```
Surprisingly, the versions scripts are identical:
```
some-mac-box:~ nwani$ diff /private/var/tmp/_bazel_nwani/c8db850cfe278c8297aabaa8ebedf47a/execroot/org_tensorflow/bazel-out/darwin-opt/bin/tensorflow/contrib/lite/toco/python/tensorflow_wrap_toco_versionscript.lds /private/var/tmp/_bazel_nwani/c8db850cfe278c8297aabaa8ebedf47a/execroot/org_tensorflow/bazel-out/darwin-opt/bin/tensorflow/contrib/tensorrt/wrap_conversion_versionscript.lds
2c2
< init_tensorflow_wrap_toco
---
> init_wrap_conversion
```
